D1.name: Anaphaa Yoga
D1.description: There are planets other than Sun in the 12th house from Moon
D1.benefit: You will become a king with good looks. Your body is likely free from disease. You are a person of character and have great reputation. You are surrounded by comforts.

D1.name: Asubha Yoga
D1.description: Lagna has malefics or has “paapa kartari or maleefics in 12th and 2nd house from Lagna.
D1.benefit: One born with this yoga has many desires and is sinful and enjoys the wealth of others.

D1.name: Bhaarathi Yoga
D1.description: If the lord of the sign occupied in navamsa by 2nd, 5th or 11th lord exalted and joins the 9th lord, then this yoga is present.
D1.benefit: One born with this yoga is a great scholar. Person is intelligent, religious, good-looking and famous. Bhaarathi is another name of Saraswathi, the goddess of learning.

D1.name: Duradhara Yoga
D1.description: There are planets other than Sun in the 2nd and 12th houses from Moon.
D1.benefit: You will enjoy many pleasures. You are charitable. You will wealth and vehicles. You will have good servants.

D1.name: Sarpa Yoga
D1.description: Three quadrants are occupied by natural malefic planets.
D1.benefit: One born with this yoga is miserable, unhappy, cruel, poor and dependent on others for food. This is a very bad combination.

D1.name: Subha Yoga
D1.description: Lagna has benefics or has “subha kartari – benefics in 12th and 2nd house from Lagna.
D1.benefit: One born with this yoga has eloquence, good looks and character

D1.name: Sunaphaa Yoga
D1.description: There are planets other than Sun in the 2nd house from Moon
D1.benefit: You will become a king or an equal. You are intelligent, wealthy and famous. You will have self-earned wealth.

D1.name: Ubhayachara Yoga
D1.description: There are planets other than Moon in the 2nd and 12th houses from Sun
D1.benefit: You will have all comforts. You will be like a king or an equal

D1.name: Veenaa Yoga
D1.description: The seven planets occupy exactly 7 distinct signs among them.
D1.benefit: One born with this yoga likes music, dance and songs. This person has many servants. This person is wealthy, skillful and a leader of men. Veenaa is a stringed musical instrument. This is also called Vallaki yoga by some authors.

D1.name: Vesai Yoga
D1.description: There is a planet other than Moon in the 2nd house from Sun
D1.benefit: You will have a balanced outlook. You are truthful, tall and sluggish. You will be happy and comfortable even with little wealth.

D1.name: Vosi Yoga
D1.description: There is a planet other than Moon in the 12th house from Sun
D1.benefit: You will be skillful, charitable, famous, learned and strong.

D2.name: Adhi Yoga
D2.description: Natural benefics occupy 6th, 7th and 8th from Moon
D2.benefit: You may become a king or a minister or an army chief, depending on the strength of the planets involved

D2.name: Amala Yoga
D2.description: There are only natural benefics present in the 10th house from lagna or Moon.
D2.benefit: One born with this yoga has ever-lasting fame. The person is respected by kings. Person has luxuries and is virtuous. Person helps others. Amala means pure. Because the 10th house shows one's' conduct in society, situation of only benefics there makes one’s conduct in the society very pure.

D2.name: Daama Yoga
D2.description: The seven planets occupy exactly 6 distinct signs among them.
D2.benefit: One born with this yoga is very rich and famous. This person has many children. This person has many gems. This person helps others. Daama means a wreath. Some authors call this Daamini yoga.

D2.name: Hamsa Yoga
D2.description: Jupiter should be in Sagitarius, Pisces or Capricornn and he should be in 1st, 4th, 7th or 10th from lagna.
D2.benefit: You are a great man of ethery nature. You are swan-like. You have spiritual strength and purity. You are respected by everyone. You are very passionate. You may become a king. You may have all comforts. You enjoy life fully. You are a clever conversationalist and endowed with good speech.

D2.name: Vasumati Yoga
D2.description: If benefics occupy upachayas, then this yoga is present.
D2.benefit: For it to give full results, malefics should not occupy upachayas and the benefics occupying upachayas should be strong. One born with this yoga has abundant wealth. Vasumati means earth.

D11.name: Sasa Yoga
D11.description: Saturn should be in Capricorn, Aquariius or Libra and he should be in 1st, 4th, 7th or 10th from lagna
D11.benefit: You are a great person of airy nature. You are rabbit-like. You are wise and enjoy wandering. You are comfortable in forests, mountains and forts. You are valorous and have a slender build. You know the weaknesses of others. You are lively, but have some vacillation. You are charitable.

D5.name: Paasa Yoga
D5.description: The seven planets occupy exactly 5 distinct signs among them.
D5.benefit: One born with this yoga has the risk of being imprisoned. This person is capable in their work. This person is talkataive. This person has many servants. This person lacks character. Paasa means a noose.

D8.name: Mridanga Yoga
D8.description: If (1) there are planets in own and exaltation signs in quadrants and trines and (2) lagna lord is strong, then this yoga is present.
D8.benefit: One born with this yoga is a king or an equal and is happy. Mridanga is a rich and elegant percussion instrument popular in south India.

D12.name: Sarala Yoga
D12.description: If the 8th lord occupies the 8th house, then this yoga is present.
D12.benefit: One born with this yoga is long-lived, fearless, learned, celebrated and prosperous. Person is a terror to his enemies. Sarala means straight-forward.

D3.name: Bheri Yoga
D3.description: ]If (1) the 9th lord is strong and (2) 1st, 2nd, 7th and 12th houses are occupied by planets, then this yoga is present. Alternately, this is yoga is present if (1) the 9th lord is strong and (2) Jupiter, Venus and lagna lord are in mutual quadrants.
D3.benefit: One born with this yoga is blessed with wealth, spouse and children. Person can be a king. Person has fame and character. Person is virtuous and religious. Person enjoys pleasures. Bheri means a kettledrum.

D3.name: guru_mangala_yoga
D3.description: If Jupiter and Mars are together or in the 7th house from each other, then this yoga is present.
D3.benefit: One born with this yoga is righteous and energetic. The person's 'energies are channelled in dharmic paths.

D3.name: Kaahala Yoga
D3.description: If (1) the 4th lord and Jupiter32 are in mutual quadrants and (2) lagna lord is strong, then this yoga is present. Alternately, this yoga is present if the 4th lord is exalted or in own sign and the 10th lord joins him.
D3.benefit: One born with this yoga is strong, bold, cunning and leads a large army. Person owns a few villages. Kaahala means excessive. It also means mischievous.

D16.name: Brahma Yoga
D16.description: If benefics occupy the 4th, 10th and 11th houses counted from lagna lord, then this yoga is present. Another variation of Brahma yoga: If (1) Jupiter is in a quadrant from the 9th lord, (2) Venus is in a quadrant from the 11th lord, and, (3) Mercury is in a quadrant from the 1st lord or 10th lord, then this yoga is present.
D16.benefit: One born with this yoga is happy, learned and blessed with wealth and children. Brahma is the creator of this universe. Lagna rules birth and the Creator is represented in a chart by lagna lord.

D16.name: Kalaanidhi Yoga
D16.description: If (1) Jupiter is in the 2nd house or the 5th house and (2) he is conjoined or aspected by Mercury and Venus, then this yoga is present.
D16.benefit: One born with this yoga is endowed with character, happiness, good health, wealth and learning. Person is respected by kings. Kalaanidhi means a treasure of arts and skills.

D16.name: Sreenaatha Yoga
D16.description: If (1) the 7th lord is exalted in 10th and (2) 10th lord is with 9th lord, then this yoga is present.
D16.benefit: One born with this yoga becomes a great king equal to Indra – king of gods. Sreenaatha means the lord of great wealth and prosperity. It also means Vishnu.

D6.name: Kedaara Yoga
D6.description: The seven planets occupy exactly 4 distinct signs among them.
D6.benefit: One born with this yoga is an agriculturist. This person is happy wealthy and helpful to others. Kedaara means a field.

D6.name: Koorma Yoga
D6.description: If (1) the 5th, 6th and 7th houses are occupied by benefics who are in own, exaltation or friendly signs and (2) the 1st, 3rd and 11th houses are occupied by malefics who are in own or exaltation signs, then this yoga is present.
D6.benefit: One born with this yoga becomes a king. Person has piety and character. Person is happy, helpful and famous. Koorma means a tortoise.

D6.name: Matsya Yoga
D6.description: If (1) benefics are in lagna and 9th, (2) some planets are in 5th, and, (3) malefics are in chaturasras (4th and 8th houses), then this yoga is present.
D6.benefit: One born with this yoga becomes an astrologer or a seer. Person is a personification of kindness, character and intelligence. Person is strong and good-looking. Person is famous and learned. Person is a tapasvi (austere pursuer). Matsya means a fish.

D81.name: Harsha Yoga
D81.description: If the 6th lord occupies the 6th house, then this yoga is present.
D81.benefit: One born with this yoga is happy, strong, good-natured and invincible. Harsha means joyous.

D81.name: Pushkala Yoga
D81.description: If (1) lagna lord is with Moon, (2) dispositor of Moon is in a quadrant or in the house of an adhimitra (good friend), (2) dispositor of Moon aspects lagna, and, (4) there is a planet in lagna, then this yoga is present.
D81.benefit: One born with this yoga is eloquent, wealthy, famous and respected by kings. Pushkala means abundant.

D30.name: Jaya Yoga
D30.description: If (1) the 10th lord is in deep exaltation and (2) the 6th lord is debilitated, then this yoga is present.
D30.benefit: One born with this yoga is happy, successful, victorious over enemies and long-lived. Jaya means victorious.

D30.name: Maalavya Yoga
D30.description: Venus is in a quadrant in own sign or exaltation sign.
D30.benefit: You are a great person of watery nature. You emit a lustre akin to moonlight. You enjoy tasty food. You have luxuries. You have excellent health. You are well-versed in arts.

D30.name: Ruchaka Yoga
D30.description: Mars is in a quadrant in own sign or exaltation sign.
D30.benefit: You are a person of fiery nature. You have a lot of enthusiasm. You are a natural leader. You love to fight wars and you will be victorious over enemies. You are discriminative and a devotee of learned people. You are well-versed in occult sciences. You have good taste. You will be always successful.

D7.name: Maalaa Yoga
D7.description: Three quadrants are occupied by natural benefics.
D7.benefit: You will be always happy. You will have nice clothes, vehicles, luxuries and friendship of many women.

D7.name: Parvata Yoga
D7.description: If (1) quadrants are occupied only by benefics and (2) the 7th and 8th houses are either vacant or occupied only by benefics
D7.benefit: One born with this yoga is fortunate, eloquent, famous, charitable, easy-going and likes humour. Parvata means a mountain.

D27.name: Sankha Yoga
D27.description: If (1) lagna lord is strong and (2) 5th and 6th lords are in mutual quadrants, then this yoga is present. Alternately, this yoga is present if (1) lagna lord and 10th lord are together in a movable sign and (2) the 9th lord is strong.
D27.benefit: One born with this yoga is blessed with wealth, spouse and children. He is kind, pious, intelligent and long-lived. Sankha means a conch shell.

D24.name: Saraswathi Yoga
D24.description: If (1) each of Mercury, Jupiter and Venus occupies a quadrant or a trine or the 2nd house (not necessarily together) and (2) Jupiter is in an own or friendly or exaltation sign, then this yoga is present.
D24.benefit: One born with this yoga is very learned, skillful, intelligent, rich and famous. Person is praised by all. Saraswathi is the goddess of learning.

D10.name: Chandra Mangala Yoga
D10.description: Moon and Mars are together (in one sign).
D10.benefit: You are worldly wise and materially successful. You may earn money through unscrupulous means. You may treat mother or other women badly.

D9.name: Hari Yoga
D9.description: If benefics occupy the 2nd, 12th and 8th houses counted from the 2nd lord, then this yoga is present.
D9.benefit: One born with this yoga is happy, learned and blessed with wealth and children. Hari is a name of Lord Vishnu. The 2nd house is the house of food and money and it is a trine from karma sthana – the 10th house. It stands for sustenance and its lord represents Hari – Sustainer of Hindu Trinity – in a chart.
